<%- include('partials/head', { title: 'Privacy' }) %>
<body>
  <%- include('partials/loader') %>
  <%- include('partials/header') %>
  
  <main>
      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <h2>Privacy Policy</h2>
          <p>How we collect, use, and protect your information.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid" style="max-width: 880px;">
          <article class="card">
            <h3>1. Information We Collect</h3>
            <p>Depending on how you use Armora Cheats, we may collect:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Account identifiers (e.g. username, email, or ID from reseller).</li>
              <li>License and activation data (keys, subscription status).</li>
              <li>Hardware identifiers (HWID) for license protection.</li>
              <li>Basic telemetry such as loader version and error reports.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>2. How We Use Your Information</h3>
            <p>We primarily use your data to:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Validate and manage your license.</li>
              <li>Provide access to our products and features.</li>
              <li>Detect abuse, fraud, or unauthorized sharing.</li>
              <li>Improve stability, security, and performance.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>3. Data Sharing</h3>
            <p>
              We do not sell your personal data. Limited information may be shared
              with:
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li>Payment partners and resellers to verify purchases.</li>
              <li>Infrastructure providers (e.g. hosting) for service delivery.</li>
              <li>
                Authorities, if required by applicable law or to respond to legal
                requests.
              </li>
            </ul>

            <h3>4. Cookies &amp; Analytics</h3>
            <p>
              Our website may use basic analytics and cookies to understand
              traffic and improve the user experience. You can manage cookies
              through your browser settings.
            </p>

            <h3>5. Data Security</h3>
            <p>
              We apply reasonable technical and organizational measures to
              protect your data. However, no system is 100% secure and we cannot
              guarantee absolute protection.
            </p>

            <h3>6. Data Retention</h3>
            <p>
              We retain data only as long as necessary for the purposes described
              in this Policy or as required by law. License and HWID information
              may be kept for fraud prevention and auditing.
            </p>

            <h3>7. Your Rights</h3>
            <p>
              Depending on your region, you may have rights to request access,
              correction, or deletion of certain data. Contact us via support if
              you wish to exercise these rights, and we will evaluate your
              request.
            </p>

            <h3>8. Changes to This Policy</h3>
            <p>
              We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. The latest version
              will always be available on this page. Your continued use of our
              services after changes become effective constitutes acceptance.
            </p>

            <h3>9. Contact</h3>
            <p>
              If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, please reach out
              via our support page or official community channels.
            </p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>
  
  <%- include('partials/footer') %>
